data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider deprecated synchronous query/save APIs and required an explicit opt-in (`EnableSyncOverAsync`) to keep them working. **In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed entirely.** Every synchronous LINQ operator (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` against the Cosmos provider now throws an `InvalidOperationException` at runtime.

### Fix — convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return `Task<T>` / `Task`, mark methods `async`
- `ToList()` → `ToListAsync()`, `First()` → `FirstAsync()`, `Count()` → `CountAsync()`, `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()`
- Remove any `EnableSyncOverAsync` configuration — it no longer exists

This will ripple up through your call chain; every caller must also `await` these methods. The Cosmos DB SDK is inherently async, so there is no supported synchronous path in EF Core 11.
